  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key prevention strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Implementing strict identification procedures\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Penalties for non-compliance:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential business license revocation\n\n5. Collaborative approaches:\n- Information sharing between financial institutions\n- International law enforcement cooperation\n- Cross-border regulatory coordination\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and enforcement mechanisms.",
